# ⚙️ COA Concept 3: Vector Processors

🔥 Important HPC + AI concept.

---

## 1️⃣ Simple Idea

Vector processors execute same operation on entire array/vector together.

---

## Example

Instead of:

```text id="x3z1rm"
A1+B1
A2+B2
A3+B3
```

One vector instruction handles all.

---

## 🧠 Real-World Analogy

Teacher giving same instruction to full classroom.

---

## Why Useful?

✔ scientific computing
✔ graphics
✔ AI workloads

---

## 🔗 Connection

Similar idea to:

👉 SIMD

---

## 🎯 Placement Question

**Q: Why vector processors are fast for AI?**

👉 Because they efficiently process large datasets in parallel.

---

## 🧠 Memory Trick

```text id="9j6wtr"
One operation on whole vector
```

---

# ⚙️ COA Concept 4: AI Model Parallelism

🔥 Modern AI infrastructure topic.

---

## 1️⃣ Problem

Huge AI models may not fit on one GPU.

---

## Solution

Split model across multiple devices.

---

## Types

---

## 🔹 Data Parallelism

Same model on many GPUs.

Different data chunks.

---

## 🔹 Model Parallelism

Different parts of model on different GPUs.

---

## 🧠 Real-World Analogy

Big project divided among teams.

---

## Why Important?

Large AI models require:

✔ huge memory
✔ massive compute power

---

## 🎯 Placement Question

**Q: Why model parallelism needed?**

👉 Because very large AI models cannot fit into one device’s memory.

---

## 🧠 Memory Trick

```text id="n2q8py"
Big model → split across GPUs
```

